Given the number n > 0. Find the amount: 1 + 1/2 + 1/3 + 1/4 +... + 1/n
Write a function called sumOfFractionals, which takes the number n and returns the sum of fractions that have 1 in the numerator and 1 to n in the denominator. 
In a solution, use the loop 'for'. Round the amount to two decimal places.

CODE:
function sumOfFractionals(n){
let sum = 0;
for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
 sum += 1 / i;
}
 return +sum.toFixed(2);
}
console.log(sumOfFractionals(1))  // 1;
console.log(sumOfFractionals(5))  // 2.28;
console.log(sumOfFractionals(10)) // 2.93.
